en_187474_0	A group of staff of the Bandaranaike International Airport staged a protest today (Apr. 02) demanding the issues relating to their salary structure to be solved.
en_187474_1	The protest was held in front of the arrival lounge of the BIA.
en_187474_2	Authorities have deployed around 1500 from the Air Force and Commando Regiment to beef up the security there.
en_187474_3	The Secretary of the airport branch of Sri Lanka Nidahas Sevaka Sangamaya, Dinesh Perera said if they do not get a solution in near future, they would resort to a work stoppage (Pix by : Prasad Muthukuda)
